# Feature 6 (T2.5) — Synthetic Data Smoke Run

## Status: DONE

## What was implemented

### src/data/synthetic.py — CLI wiring
- Added `EvalRecord` and `ErrorType` imports (needed for candidate loading)
- Added `_load_retry_candidates(path)` helper: reads TrajectoryRow objects from
  a JSONL file; returns empty list with informative message if file absent
- Replaced stub `_main()` with a working CLI that:
  - Accepts `--candidates` (default: data/analysis/retry_candidates.jsonl)
  - Accepts `--output` (default: data/processed/synthetic_train.jsonl)
  - Loads candidates with empty-list fallback
  - Calls `generate_from_retry_candidates()` with smoke/dry-run flags
  - Writes JSONL + SHA-256 fingerprint on non-dry-run runs

### docs/execution/NOTEBOOKS.md — notebook 08 row updated
- Added T2.5 smoke run note: dry-run OK, smoke write OK, absent
  retry_candidates.jsonl is expected (dependency on #22 / notebook 06)

## Commands run and output

```
$ python3 -m src.data.synthetic --smoke --dry-run
[synthetic] smoke=True, dry_run=True
[synthetic] output=data/processed/synthetic_train.jsonl
[synthetic] data/analysis/retry_candidates.jsonl not found — using empty candidate list
[dry-run] examples to generate: 0
[dry-run] estimated tokens: 0
[dry-run] estimated cost: $0.0000

$ python3 -m src.data.synthetic --smoke
[synthetic] smoke=True, dry_run=False
[synthetic] output=data/processed/synthetic_train.jsonl
[synthetic] data/analysis/retry_candidates.jsonl not found — using empty candidate list
[synthetic] wrote 0 examples -> data/processed/synthetic_train.jsonl
[synthetic] fingerprint -> data/processed/synthetic_train.sha256
```

